[Data by country, area, or territory for 8 Nov 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20NOV8_1636486574.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 8.6% cases and 16.1% deaths in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 94.35 million cases. Brazil reported over 11 000 cases over the last 24 hours, while the USA and Canada did not report any cases, among others. A total of 4 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 5 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 73.2% of daily case numbers and 62.7% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 78.98 million cases. Some countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Spain, Belgium, and Switzerland, among others. 28 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 5 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 4.4% of daily case numbers and 6.2% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 16.47 million cases. Iran (7554) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours followed by Jordan. Iraq, Lebanon, Egypt, and Libya, who reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Afghanistan, and Djibouti among others did not report cases over the last 24 hours, while Somalia and Sudan have not reported any cases over the last many days.

- The African region reported 0.36% of daily case numbers and 1.1% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 6.17 million cases. All countries reported less than 500 cases. Many countries including Botswana, Ghana, Malawi, Gabon, Guinea, and Mauritius among others, did not report cases over the last 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 7% of daily case numbers and 7.1% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 9.6 million cases. Vietnam, reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 7000 cases), followed by Malaysia, Philippines, Singapore, South Korea, Australia, and Lao PDR.

- The South East Asia region reported 6.2% of the daily newly reported cases and 6.6% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 44.14 million cases. India is dominant reporting over 11 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Thailand (7592). Indonesia, Nepal, and Bangladesh reported less than 500 cases. Myanmar, Maldives and Sri Lanka did not report cases over the last 24 hours.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 8 Nov 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

